headline: The S&P 500 Entered a Correction Last Week. 2 Winning Stocks to Buy While They're Still on Sale
summary: Following on the heels of the Nasdaq Composite, the S&P 500 entered a correction last week, meaning the broad-market index fell at least 10% from its recent peak.  After the market seemed to initially cheer the election of President Donald Trump, it quickly reversed course, and the S&P 500 fell to its lowest level in six months.  Target (NYSE: TGT) stock has fallen in the recent correction, but it's been struggling for a while, and is down more than 50% over the last three years.
